item.title: The Mysterious Case of Dancing Penguins and Their Secret Tango Academy
item.dc:creator: Bella Brennan
item.description: Scientists have discovered that penguins in Antarctica have been secretly learning the tango and forming underground dance academies. These sophisticated birds apparently gather at midnight to practice their elaborate choreography under the southern lights.
